    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1866-11-30T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1866-11-30T00:00:00-05:00" n="372"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d372">
                <head>
                    <persName type="from">Mr. Seward</persName> to <persName type="to">Mr.
                        Burlingame</persName>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 175.]</seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <hi rend="italic"
                                >Washington</hi>,</placeName>
                        <date calendar="gregorian" when="1866-11-30">
                            <hi rend="italic">November</hi> 30, 1866</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: The Messrs. Baring, in reply to a letter from the
                    department on the subject, have stated that it would not be convenient for them
                    to purchase bills <pb facs="0487" n="419" xml:id="pg_419"/> on you for the
                    surplus of the Chinese indemnity. They suggest that you be authorized to
                    purchase bills on London with that surplus, and remit the same to them.</p>
                <p>The department has informed them that this suggestion, if adopted at all,
                    probably would not be carried into effect until after the next session of
                    Congress.</p>
                <p>I am, sir, your obedient servant,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>WILLIAM H. SEWARD.</signed>
                </closer>
                <postscript>
                    <p>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Anson Burlingame</hi>, Esq., <hi rend="italic">&amp;c.,
                            &amp;c., &amp;c.</hi>
                    </p>
                </postscript>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
